item.title: How to make a command that teleports you to a place
item.dc:creator: @Syfal Syfal
item.description:
@Syfal wrote:

Please be more specific next time, it makes helping people a little easier

Anyway, here is a teleport command for 317. Add it into Client.java:

if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("thieving"))
	{
		teleportToX = ####;
		teleportToY = ####;
	}

And for 508 if you need (or ever need) it:

 if(cmd[0].equals("thieving")) 
{
                     p.teleportTo(####, ####, 0, 0, 0, 8939, 8941, 1576, 0, 1577, 0);
}

Add it into Commands.java

Just replace the #### with the coordinates of where your thieving area is.
